Everything is in the box.
So sing it!”
His karma-mastery technique was always perfectly comprehensible and accurate, but it was never dictatorial or exaggerated.
No matter what the music level was, he always raised it.
John Frayn Turner wrote about it:
If there ever was a leader who was supposed to become a knight, it was Vernon Handley.
I knew him well during the two decades he led the Guildford Philharmonic from 1962 to 1982.
I have written about more than 100 of his concerts over the past forty years, but it has never disappointed me, and often inspired me.
